Detectives have arrested a 39-year-old man on suspicion of murder after a man fell more than 80ft to his death from a block of flats last night.

A man in his early 30s died in the early hours of this morning after falling from the eighth floor of the Paradise House tower block in the Foleshill area of Coventry.

He had been found lying injured by a passer by at around 11.20pm.

