Although he was taken to hospital, he died shortly after midnight.

A man was arrested on suspicion of murder after handing himself into police this morning.

The area around the flats remained cordoned off today while detectives carried out a forensics search and made door to door enquiries.

West Midlands Police Superintendent Nick Walton said: 'We're still in the very early stages of this investigation and our enquiries to understand exactly what happened are ongoing.

'I want to reassure people that this is being treated as an isolated incident and we now have a named suspect in custody.

'But we are still keen to hear from any witnesses or anyone who may be able to help us piece together the events of yesterday evening.

